# To view the cookies used by Chrome:
# 1. Go to bloomberg.com and log in
# 2. Open DevTools (Press F12 or right-click anywhere on the page → Inspect)
# 3. Go to Application tab → Cookies → https://www.bloomberg.com
#    This will list all the cookies. We need to copy all of them.
#
# To copy all the cookies from Chrome:
# 1. Go to bloomberg.com and log in
# 2. Open DevTools (Press F12 or right-click anywhere on the page → Inspect)
# 3. Click the Console tab
# 4. Scroll to the bottom and click next to the > prompt
#    If the prompt is not visible, press Ctrl+L to clear the console.
# 5. Type: copy(document.cookie) and press Enter
# 6. Nothing visible will happen — the cookies are silently copied to your clipboard
# 7. Copy this file to bloomberg.txt and replace the line below with your cookies
# 8. Make sure bloomberg.txt is in .gitignore
